See also blog post and Actions overview document.

The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

member.summary: The object that helped the agent perform the action. e.g. John wrote a book with a pen.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Action.Location
member.summary: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Action.Object
member.summary: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). e.g. John read a book.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Action.Participant
member.summary: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. e.g. John wrote a book with Steve.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Action.Result
member.summary: The result produced in the action. e.g. John wrote a book.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Action.StartTime
member.summary:
The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Article.Speakable
member.summary:
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.

The speakable property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:

1.) id-value URL references - uses id-value of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of speakable has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.

2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, eg. via class attribute. Use the cssSelector property.

3.) XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the xpath property.

For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For this we define a supporting type, SpeakableSpecification which is defined to be a possible value of the speakable property.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Article.WordCount
member.summary: The number of words in the text of the Article.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.BreadcrumbList
member.summary:
A BreadcrumbList is an ItemList consisting of a chain of linked Web pages, typically described using at least their URL and their name, and typically ending with the current page.

The position property is used to reconstruct the order of the items in a BreadcrumbList The convention is that a breadcrumb list has an itemListOrder of ItemListOrderAscending (lower values listed first), and that the first items in this list correspond to the "top" or beginning of the breadcrumb trail, e.g. with a site or section homepage. The specific values of 'position' are not assigned meaning for a BreadcrumbList, but they should be integers, e.g. beginning with '1' for the first item in the list.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.Campground
member.summary:
A camping site, campsite, or campground is a place used for overnight stay in the outdoors. In British English a campsite is an area, usually divided into a number of pitches, where people can camp overnight using tents or camper vans or caravans; this British English use of the word is synonymous with the American English expression campground. In American English the term campsite generally means an area where an individual, family, group, or military unit can pitch a tent or parks a camper; a campground may contain many campsites (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Campsite).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CivicStructure.OpeningHours
member.summary:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.

  • Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
  • If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CivicStructureAndEmergencyService.OpeningHours
member.summary:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.

  • Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
  • If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem
member.summary: See CreativeWork, ItemList, ListItem for more information.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.About
member.summary: The subject matter of the content.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AccessibilityAPI
member.summary: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AccessibilityControl
member.summary: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AccessibilityFeature
member.summary: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AccessibilityHazard
member.summary: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AccessibilitySummary
member.summary: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed."

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AccessMode
member.summary: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Expected values include: auditory, tactile, textual, visual, colorDependent, chartOnVisual, chemOnVisual, diagramOnVisual, mathOnVisual, musicOnVisual, textOnVisual.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AccessModeSufficient
member.summary: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Expected values include: auditory, tactile, textual, visual.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AccountablePerson
member.summary: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AggregateRating
member.summary: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AlternativeHeadline
member.summary: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.AssociatedMedia
member.summary: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Audience
member.summary: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Audio
member.summary: An embedded audio object.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Author
member.summary: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Award
member.summary: An award won by or for this item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Character
member.summary: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Citation
member.summary: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Comment
member.summary: Comments, typically from users.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.CommentCount
member.summary: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.ContentLocation
member.summary: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.ContentRating
member.summary: Official rating of a piece of content—for example,'MPAA PG-13'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.ContentReferenceTime
member.summary: The specific time described by a creative work, for works (e.g. articles, video objects etc.) that emphasise a particular moment within an Event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Contributor
member.summary: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.CopyrightHolder
member.summary: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.CopyrightYear
member.summary: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Correction
member.summary: Indicates a correction to a CreativeWork, either via a CorrectionComment, textually or in another document.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Creator
member.summary: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.DateCreated
member.summary: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.DateModified
member.summary: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.DatePublished
member.summary: Date of first broadcast/publication.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.DiscussionUrl
member.summary: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Editor
member.summary: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.EducationalAlignment
member.summary: An alignment to an established educational framework.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.EducationalUse
member.summary: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Encoding
member.summary: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.EncodingFormat
member.summary:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see IANA site and MDN reference) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).

In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, encoding can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular encodingFormat information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.ExampleOfWork
member.summary: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Expires
member.summary: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a VideoObject or NewsArticle whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a ClaimReview fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Funder
member.summary: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Genre
member.summary: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.HasPart
member.summary: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Headline
member.summary: Headline of the article.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.InLanguage
member.summary: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.InteractionStatistic
member.summary: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.InteractivityType
member.summary: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.IsAccessibleForFree
member.summary: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.IsBasedOn
member.summary: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.IsFamilyFriendly
member.summary: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.IsPartOf
member.summary: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Item
member.summary: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists').

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.ItemListElement
member.summary:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements. Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.ItemListOrder
member.summary: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Keywords
member.summary: Keywords or tags used to describe this content. Multiple entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.LearningResourceType
member.summary: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.License
member.summary: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.LocationCreated
member.summary: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.MainEntity
member.summary: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Material
member.summary: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Mentions
member.summary: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.NextItem
member.summary: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.NumberOfItems
member.summary: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Offers
member.summary: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Position
member.summary: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.PreviousItem
member.summary: A link to the ListItem that preceeds the current one.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Producer
member.summary: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, tv/radio series etc.).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Provider
member.summary: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Publication
member.summary: A publication event associated with the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Publisher
member.summary: The publisher of the creative work.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.PublisherImprint
member.summary: The publishing division which published the comic.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.PublishingPrinciples
member.summary:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via URL) a document describing the editorial principles of an Organization (or individual e.g. a Person writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a CreativeWork (e.g. NewsArticle) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a funder) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.RecordedAt
member.summary: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.ReleasedEvent
member.summary: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Review
member.summary: A review of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.SchemaVersion
member.summary: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. For example, a document could declare a schemaVersion using an URL such as http://schema.org/version/2.0/ if precise indication of schema version was required by some application.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.SdDatePublished
member.summary: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside sdPublisher

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.SdLicense
member.summary: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.SdPublisher
member.summary: Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The sdPublisher property helps make such practices more explicit.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.SourceOrganization
member.summary: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.SpatialCoverage
member.summary: The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Sponsor
member.summary: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.TemporalCoverage
member.summary: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Text
member.summary: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.ThumbnailUrl
member.summary: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.TimeRequired
member.summary: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'P30M', 'P1H25M'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.TranslationOfWork
member.summary: The work that this work has been translated from. e.g. is a translationOf On the Origin of Species

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Translator
member.summary: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.TypicalAgeRange
member.summary: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Version
member.summary: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.Video
member.summary: An embedded video object.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.WorkExample
member.summary: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. eg. The paperback edition, first edition, or eBook.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndItemListAndListItem.WorkTranslation
member.summary: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. e.g. has an English workTranslation Journey to the West,a German workTranslation Monkeys Pilgerfahrt and a Vietnamese translation Ty du k bnh kho.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AccessibilityAPI
member.summary: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AccessibilityControl
member.summary: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AccessibilityFeature
member.summary: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AccessibilityHazard
member.summary: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AccessibilitySummary
member.summary: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed."

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AccessMode
member.summary: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Expected values include: auditory, tactile, textual, visual, colorDependent, chartOnVisual, chemOnVisual, diagramOnVisual, mathOnVisual, musicOnVisual, textOnVisual.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AccessModeSufficient
member.summary: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Expected values include: auditory, tactile, textual, visual.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AccountablePerson
member.summary: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AggregateRating
member.summary: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AlternativeHeadline
member.summary: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.AssociatedMedia
member.summary: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Audience
member.summary: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Audio
member.summary: An embedded audio object.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Author
member.summary: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Award
member.summary: An award won by or for this item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Character
member.summary: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Citation
member.summary: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Comment
member.summary: Comments, typically from users.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.CommentCount
member.summary: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.ContentLocation
member.summary: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.ContentRating
member.summary: Official rating of a piece of content—for example,'MPAA PG-13'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.ContentReferenceTime
member.summary: The specific time described by a creative work, for works (e.g. articles, video objects etc.) that emphasise a particular moment within an Event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Contributor
member.summary: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.CopyrightHolder
member.summary: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.CopyrightYear
member.summary: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Correction
member.summary: Indicates a correction to a CreativeWork, either via a CorrectionComment, textually or in another document.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Creator
member.summary: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.DateCreated
member.summary: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.DateModified
member.summary: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.DatePublished
member.summary: Date of first broadcast/publication.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.DiscussionUrl
member.summary: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Editor
member.summary: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.EducationalAlignment
member.summary: An alignment to an established educational framework.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.EducationalUse
member.summary: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Encoding
member.summary: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.EncodingFormat
member.summary:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see IANA site and MDN reference) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).

In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, encoding can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular encodingFormat information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.ExampleOfWork
member.summary: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Expires
member.summary: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a VideoObject or NewsArticle whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a ClaimReview fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Funder
member.summary: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Genre
member.summary: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.HasPart
member.summary: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Headline
member.summary: Headline of the article.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.InLanguage
member.summary: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.InteractionStatistic
member.summary: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.InteractivityType
member.summary: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.IsAccessibleForFree
member.summary: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.IsBasedOn
member.summary: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.IsFamilyFriendly
member.summary: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.IsPartOf
member.summary: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Item
member.summary: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists').

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Keywords
member.summary: Keywords or tags used to describe this content. Multiple entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.LearningResourceType
member.summary: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.License
member.summary: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.LocationCreated
member.summary: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.MainEntity
member.summary: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Material
member.summary: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Mentions
member.summary: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.NextItem
member.summary: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Offers
member.summary: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Position
member.summary: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.PreviousItem
member.summary: A link to the ListItem that preceeds the current one.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Producer
member.summary: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, tv/radio series etc.).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Provider
member.summary: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Publication
member.summary: A publication event associated with the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Publisher
member.summary: The publisher of the creative work.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.PublisherImprint
member.summary: The publishing division which published the comic.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.PublishingPrinciples
member.summary:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via URL) a document describing the editorial principles of an Organization (or individual e.g. a Person writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a CreativeWork (e.g. NewsArticle) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a funder) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.RecordedAt
member.summary: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.ReleasedEvent
member.summary: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Review
member.summary: A review of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.SchemaVersion
member.summary: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. For example, a document could declare a schemaVersion using an URL such as http://schema.org/version/2.0/ if precise indication of schema version was required by some application.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.SdDatePublished
member.summary: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside sdPublisher

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.SdLicense
member.summary: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.SdPublisher
member.summary: Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The sdPublisher property helps make such practices more explicit.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.SourceOrganization
member.summary: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.SpatialCoverage
member.summary: The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Sponsor
member.summary: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.TemporalCoverage
member.summary: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Text
member.summary: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.ThumbnailUrl
member.summary: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.TimeRequired
member.summary: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'P30M', 'P1H25M'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.TranslationOfWork
member.summary: The work that this work has been translated from. e.g. is a translationOf On the Origin of Species

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Translator
member.summary: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.TypicalAgeRange
member.summary: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Version
member.summary: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.Video
member.summary: An embedded video object.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.WorkExample
member.summary: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. eg. The paperback edition, first edition, or eBook.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndListItem.WorkTranslation
member.summary: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. e.g. has an English workTranslation Journey to the West,a German workTranslation Monkeys Pilgerfahrt and a Vietnamese translation Ty du k bnh kho.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.Review
member.summary: A review of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.SchemaVersion
member.summary: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. For example, a document could declare a schemaVersion using an URL such as http://schema.org/version/2.0/ if precise indication of schema version was required by some application.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.SdDatePublished
member.summary: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside sdPublisher

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.SdLicense
member.summary: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.SdPublisher
member.summary: Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The sdPublisher property helps make such practices more explicit.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.SourceOrganization
member.summary: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.SpatialCoverage
member.summary: The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.Sponsor
member.summary: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.TemporalCoverage
member.summary: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.Text
member.summary: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.ThumbnailUrl
member.summary: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.TimeRequired
member.summary: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'P30M', 'P1H25M'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.TranslationOfWork
member.summary: The work that this work has been translated from. e.g. is a translationOf On the Origin of Species

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.Translator
member.summary: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.TypicalAgeRange
member.summary: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.Version
member.summary: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.Video
member.summary: An embedded video object.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.WorkExample
member.summary: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. eg. The paperback edition, first edition, or eBook.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndSeries.WorkTranslation
member.summary: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. e.g. has an English workTranslation Journey to the West,a German workTranslation Monkeys Pilgerfahrt and a Vietnamese translation Ty du k bnh kho.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.ApplicationCategory
member.summary: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.ApplicationSubCategory
member.summary: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.ApplicationSuite
member.summary: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.AvailableOnDevice
member.summary: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.CharacterAttribute
member.summary: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.CountriesNotSupported
member.summary: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.CountriesSupported
member.summary: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.DownloadUrl
member.summary: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.FeatureList
member.summary: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.FileSize
member.summary: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.GameItem
member.summary: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.GameLocation
member.summary: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.InstallUrl
member.summary: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.MemoryRequirements
member.summary: Minimum memory requirements.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.NumberOfPlayers
member.summary: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.OperatingSystem
member.summary: Operating systems supported (Windows 7, OSX 10.6, Android 1.6).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.Permissions
member.summary: Permission(s) required to run the app (for example, a mobile app may require full internet access or may run only on wifi).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.ProcessorRequirements
member.summary: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.Quest
member.summary: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.ReleaseNotes
member.summary: Description of what changed in this version.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.Screenshot
member.summary: A link to a screenshot image of the app.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.SoftwareAddOn
member.summary: Additional content for a software application.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.SoftwareHelp
member.summary: Software application help.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.SoftwareRequirements
member.summary: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (Examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.SoftwareVersion
member.summary: Version of the software instance.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.StorageRequirements
member.summary: Storage requirements (free space required).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.GameAndSoftwareApplication.SupportingData
member.summary: Supporting data for a SoftwareApplication.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization
member.summary: See LocalBusiness, MedicalOrganization for more information.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.CurrenciesAccepted
member.summary:
The currency accepted.

Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.HealthPlanNetworkId
member.summary: Name or unique ID of network. (Networks are often reused across different insurance plans).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.IsAcceptingNewPatients
member.summary: Whether the provider is accepting new patients.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.MedicalSpecialty
member.summary: A medical specialty of the provider.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.OpeningHours
member.summary:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.

  • Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
  • If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.PaymentAccepted
member.summary: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.PriceRange
member.summary: The price range of the business, for example $$$.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace
member.summary: See LocalBusiness, Organization, Place for more information.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.ActionableFeedbackPolicy
member.summary: For a NewsMediaOrganization or other news-related Organization, a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsrooms), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.AdditionalProperty
member.summary:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.

Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Address
member.summary: Physical address of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.AggregateRating
member.summary: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Alumni
member.summary: Alumni of an organization.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.AmenityFeature
member.summary: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.AreaServed
member.summary: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Award
member.summary: An award won by or for this item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.BranchCode
member.summary:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.

For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Brand
member.summary: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.ContactPoint
member.summary: A contact point for a person or organization.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.ContainedInPlace
member.summary: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.ContainsPlace
member.summary: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.CorrectionsPolicy
member.summary: For an Organization (e.g. NewsMediaOrganization), a statement describing (in news media, the newsrooms) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.CurrenciesAccepted
member.summary:
The currency accepted.

Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Department
member.summary: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.DissolutionDate
member.summary: The date that this organization was dissolved.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.DiversityPolicy
member.summary: Statement on diversity policy by an Organization e.g. a NewsMediaOrganization. For a NewsMediaOrganization, a statement describing the newsrooms diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.DiversityStaffingReport
member.summary: For an Organization (often but not necessarily a NewsMediaOrganization), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Duns
member.summary: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Email
member.summary: Email address.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Employee
member.summary: Someone working for this organization.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.EthicsPolicy
member.summary: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a NewsMediaOrganization regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a Restaurant, a page describing food source policies. In the case of a NewsMediaOrganization, an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Event
member.summary: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.FaxNumber
member.summary: The fax number.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Founder
member.summary: A person who founded this organization.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.FoundingDate
member.summary: The date that this organization was founded.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.FoundingLocation
member.summary: The place where the Organization was founded.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Funder
member.summary: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Geo
member.summary: The geo coordinates of the place.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GeospatiallyContains
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GeospatiallyCoveredBy
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GeospatiallyCovers
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GeospatiallyCrosses
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GeospatiallyDisjoint
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM)

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GeospatiallyEquals
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in DE-9IM. "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship)

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GeospatiallyIntersects
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GeospatiallyOverlaps
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GeospatiallyTouches
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM )

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GeospatiallyWithin
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.GlobalLocationNumber
member.summary: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.HasMap
member.summary: A URL to a map of the place.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.HasOfferCatalog
member.summary: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.HasPOS
member.summary: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.IsAccessibleForFree
member.summary: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.IsicV4
member.summary: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.KnowsAbout
member.summary: Of a Person, and less typically of an Organization, to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or yet relate this to educational content, events, objectives or JobPosting descriptions.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.KnowsLanguage
member.summary: Of a Person, and less typically of an Organization, to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.LegalName
member.summary: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.LeiCode
member.summary: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Location
member.summary: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Logo
member.summary: An associated logo.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.MakesOffer
member.summary: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.MaximumAttendeeCapacity
member.summary: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Member
member.summary: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.MemberOf
member.summary: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Naics
member.summary: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.NumberOfEmployees
member.summary: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.OpeningHours
member.summary:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.

  • Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
  • If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.OpeningHoursSpecification
member.summary: The opening hours of a certain place.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.OwnershipFundingInfo
member.summary: For an Organization (often but not necessarily a NewsMediaOrganization), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence. Note that the funder is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Owns
member.summary: Products owned by the organization or person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.ParentOrganization
member.summary: The larger organization that this organization is a subOrganization of, if any.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.PaymentAccepted
member.summary: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Photo
member.summary: A photograph of this place.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.PriceRange
member.summary: The price range of the business, for example $$$.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.PublicAccess
member.summary: A flag to signal that the Place is open to public visitors. If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.PublishingPrinciples
member.summary:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via URL) a document describing the editorial principles of an Organization (or individual e.g. a Person writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a CreativeWork (e.g. NewsArticle) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a funder) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Review
member.summary: A review of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Seeks
member.summary: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.SmokingAllowed
member.summary: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.SpecialOpeningHoursSpecification
member.summary:
The special opening hours of a certain place.

Use this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by openingHoursSpecification or openingHours.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Sponsor
member.summary: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.SubOrganization
member.summary: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.TaxID
member.summary: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.Telephone
member.summary: The telephone number.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.UnnamedSourcesPolicy
member.summary: For an Organization (typically a NewsMediaOrganization), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganizationAndPlace.VatID
member.summary: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

member.summary:

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.CurrenciesAccepted
member.summary:
The currency accepted.

Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

member.summary: The geo coordinates of the place.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.GeospatiallyContains
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.GeospatiallyCoveredBy
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.GeospatiallyCovers
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.GeospatiallyCrosses
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.GeospatiallyDisjoint
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM)

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.GeospatiallyEquals
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in DE-9IM. "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship)

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.GeospatiallyIntersects
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.GeospatiallyOverlaps
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.GeospatiallyTouches
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM )

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.GeospatiallyWithin
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndPlace.OpeningHours
member.summary:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.

  • Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
  • If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.
