member.name: P:Schema.NET.OrganizationAndPlace.PublishingPrinciples
member.summary:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via URL) a document describing the editorial principles of an Organization (or individual e.g. a Person writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a CreativeWork (e.g. NewsArticle) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a funder) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.AccessibilityControl

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.AccessibilitySummary
member.summary: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed."

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.AccessMode

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.AccessModeSufficient

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.AccountablePerson

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.AggregateRating

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Audio

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Award

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Character

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.ContentRating

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.EducationalUse

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Encoding

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.EncodingFormat
member.summary:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see IANA site and MDN reference) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).

In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, encoding can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular encodingFormat information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.ExampleOfWork

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Expires

For example a VideoObject or NewsArticle whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a ClaimReview fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Funder

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Genre

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Headline

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.InLanguage

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.InteractionStatistic

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.InteractivityType

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.IsPartOf

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.LearningResourceType

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Mentions

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Offers

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Position

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Producer

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Provider
member.summary: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Publication
member.summary: A publication event associated with the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Publisher

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.PublisherImprint

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.PublishingPrinciples
member.summary:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via URL) a document describing the editorial principles of an Organization (or individual e.g. a Person writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a CreativeWork (e.g. NewsArticle) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a funder) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.RecordedAt
member.summary: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.ReleasedEvent
member.summary: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Review
member.summary: A review of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.SchemaVersion
member.summary: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. For example, a document could declare a schemaVersion using an URL such as http://schema.org/version/2.0/ if precise indication of schema version was required by some application.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.SdDatePublished
member.summary: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside sdPublisher

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.SdLicense
member.summary: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.SdPublisher
member.summary: Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The sdPublisher property helps make such practices more explicit.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.SourceOrganization
member.summary: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.SpatialCoverage
member.summary: The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Sponsor
member.summary: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.TemporalCoverage
member.summary: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.Text

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWork.ThumbnailUrl

member.name: T:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkSeries
member.summary:
A CreativeWorkSeries in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. CreativeWorkSeries are usually organized into some order, often chronological. Unlike ItemList which is a general purpose data structure for lists of things, the emphasis with CreativeWorkSeries is on published materials (written e.g. books and periodicals, or media such as tv, radio and games).

Specific subtypes are available for describing TVSeries, RadioSeries, MovieSeries, BookSeries, Periodical and VideoGameSeries. In each case, the hasPart / isPartOf properties can be used to relate the CreativeWorkSeries to its parts. The general CreativeWorkSeries type serves largely just to organize these more specific and practical subtypes.

It is common for properties applicable to an item from the series to be usefully applied to the containing group. Schema.org attempts to anticipate some of these cases, but publishers should be free to apply properties of the series parts to the series as a whole wherever they seem appropriate.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DataCatalog.Dataset
member.summary: A dataset contained in this catalog.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DataCatalog.MeasurementTechnique
member.summary:
A technique or technology used in a Dataset (or DataDownload, DataCatalog), corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (described using variableMeasured). This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but rather as a high level summary for dataset discovery.

For example, if variableMeasured is: molecule concentration, measurementTechnique could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence".

If the variableMeasured is "depression rating", the measurementTechnique could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory".

If there are several variableMeasured properties recorded for some given data object, use a PropertyValue for each variableMeasured and attach the corresponding measurementTechnique.

This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but rather as a high level summary for dataset discovery.

For example, if variableMeasured is: molecule concentration, measurementTechnique could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence".

If the variableMeasured is "depression rating", the measurementTechnique could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory".

If there are several variableMeasured properties recorded for some given data object, use a PropertyValue for each variableMeasured and attach the corresponding measurementTechnique.

member.summary:
A technique or technology used in a Dataset (or DataDownload, DataCatalog), corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (described using variableMeasured). This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but rather as a high level summary for dataset discovery.

For example, if variableMeasured is: molecule concentration, measurementTechnique could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence".

If the variableMeasured is "depression rating", the measurementTechnique could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory".

If there are several variableMeasured properties recorded for some given data object, use a PropertyValue for each variableMeasured and attach the corresponding measurementTechnique.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.FollowAction
member.summary:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates polled from.

Related actions:

  • BefriendAction: Unlike BefriendAction, FollowAction implies that the connection is not necessarily reciprocal.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, FollowAction implies that the follower acts as an active agent constantly/actively polling for updates.
  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, FollowAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.
  • JoinAction: Unlike JoinAction, FollowAction implies that the agent is interested in getting updates from the object.
  • TrackAction: Unlike TrackAction, FollowAction refers to the polling of updates of all aspects of animate objects rather than the location of inanimate objects (e.g. you track a package, but you don't follow it).

member.summary:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusiness.CurrenciesAccepted
member.summary:
The currency accepted.

Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusiness.OpeningHours
member.summary:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.

  • Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
  • If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

member.summary: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.NewsArticle
member.summary:
A NewsArticle is an article whose content reports news, or provides background context and supporting materials for understanding the news.

A more detailed overview of schema.org News markup is also available.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.NewsArticle.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.NewsArticle.Dateline
member.summary:
A dateline is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.

Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using locationCreated (which represents where a work was created e.g. where a news report was written). For location depicted or described in the content, use contentLocation.

Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.NewsArticle.PrintColumn
member.summary: The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.NewsArticle.PrintEdition
member.summary: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.NewsArticle.PrintPage
member.summary: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.NewsArticle.PrintSection
member.summary: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the print section in which the article appeared.

member.summary:
An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

For GTIN-related fields, see Check Digit calculator and validation guide from GS1.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.AcceptedPaymentMethod
member.summary: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.AddOn
member.summary: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.AdvanceBookingRequirement
member.summary: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.AggregateRating
member.summary: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.AreaServed
member.summary: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

member.summary: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.AvailabilityEnds

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.AvailabilityStarts
member.summary: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.AvailableAtOrFrom
member.summary: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.AvailableDeliveryMethod

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.BusinessFunction

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.Category
member.summary: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.DeliveryLeadTime
member.summary: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.EligibleCustomerType
member.summary: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.EligibleDuration
member.summary: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.EligibleQuantity
member.summary: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.EligibleRegion
member.summary:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.

See also ineligibleRegion.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.EligibleTransactionVolume
member.summary: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.Gtin12
member.summary: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.Gtin13
member.summary: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.Gtin14
member.summary: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.Gtin8
member.summary: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.IncludesObject
member.summary: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Offer.Price
member.summary:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

  • Use the priceCurrency property (with standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
  • Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

member.summary:

Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Place.GeospatiallyContains
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Place.GeospatiallyCoveredBy
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Place.GeospatiallyCovers
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Place.GeospatiallyCrosses
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Place.GeospatiallyDisjoint
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM)

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Place.GeospatiallyEquals
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in DE-9IM. "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship)

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Place.GeospatiallyIntersects
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Place.GeospatiallyOverlaps
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Place.GeospatiallyTouches
member.summary: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM )

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Place.GeospatiallyWithin
member.summary: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in DE-9IM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.PriceSpecification.Price
member.summary:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

  • Use the priceCurrency property (with standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
  • Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.PriceSpecification.PriceCurrency
member.summary:
The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

member.summary: The date when the item becomes valid.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.PriceSpecification.ValidThrough
member.summary: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.PriceSpecification.ValueAddedTaxIncluded
member.summary: Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.PropertyValue.MeasurementTechnique
member.summary:
A technique or technology used in a Dataset (or DataDownload, DataCatalog), corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (described using variableMeasured). This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but rather as a high level summary for dataset discovery.

For example, if variableMeasured is: molecule concentration, measurementTechnique could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence".

If the variableMeasured is "depression rating", the measurementTechnique could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory".

If there are several variableMeasured properties recorded for some given data object, use a PropertyValue for each variableMeasured and attach the corresponding measurementTechnique.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.PropertyValue.PropertyID
member.summary: A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be (1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific id of the property), or (3) a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry). Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.SubscribeAction
member.summary:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates pushed to.

Related actions:

  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, SubscribeAction implies that the subscriber acts as a passive agent being constantly/actively pushed for updates.
  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.
  • JoinAction: Unlike JoinAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.TradeAction.Price
member.summary:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

  • Use the priceCurrency property (with standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
  • Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

member.summary:

Typical unit code(s): SEC for seconds

  • Note: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for seconds/0..100 km/h or seconds/0..60 mph. Simply use "SEC" for seconds and indicate the velocities in the name of the QuantitativeValue, or use valueReference with a QuantitativeValue of 0..60 mph or 0..100 km/h to specify the reference speeds.

Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet

Note: You can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Vehicle.DateVehicleFirstRegistered
member.summary: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Vehicle.DriveWheelConfiguration
member.summary: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

member.summary: The CO2 emissions in g/km. When used in combination with a QuantitativeValue, put "g/km" into the unitText property of that value, since there is no UN/CEFACT Common Code for "g/km".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Vehicle.FuelCapacity
member.summary:
The capacity of the fuel tank or in the case of electric cars, the battery. If there are multiple components for storage, this should indicate the total of all storage of the same type.

Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, GLL of US gallons, GLI for UK / imperial gallons, AMH for ampere-hours (for electrical vehicles).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Vehicle.FuelConsumption
member.summary:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).

  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Vehicle.FuelEfficiency
member.summary:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).

  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Vehicle.FuelType
member.summary: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Vehicle.KnownVehicleDamages

  • Note 4: Note that you can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Vehicle.Speed
member.summary:
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by maxValue should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.

Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot

*Note 1: Use minValue and maxValue to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero. * Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the valueReference property.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.WebPage.Speakable
member.summary:
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.

The speakable property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:

1.) id-value URL references - uses id-value of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of speakable has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.

2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, eg. via class attribute. Use the cssSelector property.

3.) XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the xpath property.

For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For this we define a supporting type, SpeakableSpecification which is defined to be a possible value of the speakable property.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.EncodingFormat
member.summary:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see IANA site and MDN reference) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).

In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, encoding can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular encodingFormat information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

For example a VideoObject or NewsArticle whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a ClaimReview fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Funder

member.summary: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Position
member.summary: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Producer

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Provider
member.summary: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Publication
member.summary: A publication event associated with the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Publisher
member.summary: The publisher of the creative work.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.PublisherImprint
member.summary: The publishing division which published the comic.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.PublishingPrinciples
member.summary:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via URL) a document describing the editorial principles of an Organization (or individual e.g. a Person writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a CreativeWork (e.g. NewsArticle) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a funder) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.RecordedAt
member.summary: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.ReleasedEvent
member.summary: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Review
member.summary: A review of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.SchemaVersion
member.summary: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. For example, a document could declare a schemaVersion using an URL such as http://schema.org/version/2.0/ if precise indication of schema version was required by some application.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.SdDatePublished
member.summary: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside sdPublisher

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.SdLicense
member.summary: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.SdPublisher
member.summary: Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The sdPublisher property helps make such practices more explicit.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.SourceOrganization
member.summary: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.SpatialCoverage
member.summary: The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Sponsor
member.summary: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.TemporalCoverage
member.summary: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Text
member.summary: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.ThumbnailUrl
member.summary: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.TimeRequired

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.TranslationOfWork

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Translator

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.TypicalAgeRange
member.summary: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Version

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndLifestyleModification.Video
member.summary: An embedded video object.

member.summary: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. e.g. has an English workTranslation Journey to the West,a German workTranslation Monkeys Pilgerfahrt and a Vietnamese translation Ty du k bnh kho.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.PublishingPrinciples
member.summary:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via URL) a document describing the editorial principles of an Organization (or individual e.g. a Person writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a CreativeWork (e.g. NewsArticle) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a funder) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.RecordedAt
member.summary: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.ReleasedEvent
member.summary: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.Review
member.summary: A review of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.SchemaVersion
member.summary: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. For example, a document could declare a schemaVersion using an URL such as http://schema.org/version/2.0/ if precise indication of schema version was required by some application.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.SdDatePublished
member.summary: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside sdPublisher

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.SdLicense
member.summary: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.SdPublisher
member.summary: Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The sdPublisher property helps make such practices more explicit.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.SourceOrganization
member.summary: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.SpatialCoverage
member.summary: The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.Sponsor
member.summary: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.TemporalCoverage
member.summary: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.Text
member.summary: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.ThumbnailUrl
member.summary: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.TimeRequired
member.summary: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'P30M', 'P1H25M'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.TranslationOfWork
member.summary: The work that this work has been translated from. e.g. is a translationOf On the Origin of Species

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.Translator
member.summary: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.TypicalAgeRange
member.summary: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.Version
member.summary: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.Video
member.summary: An embedded video object.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.WorkExample
member.summary: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. eg. The paperback edition, first edition, or eBook.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.CreativeWorkAndPhysicalActivity.WorkTranslation
member.summary: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. e.g. has an English workTranslation Journey to the West,a German workTranslation Monkeys Pilgerfahrt and a Vietnamese translation Ty du k bnh kho.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization
member.summary: See LocalBusiness, Organization for more information.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.ActionableFeedbackPolicy
member.summary: For a NewsMediaOrganization or other news-related Organization, a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsrooms), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Address
member.summary: Physical address of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.AggregateRating
member.summary: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Alumni
member.summary: Alumni of an organization.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.AreaServed
member.summary: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Award
member.summary: An award won by or for this item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Brand
member.summary: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.ContactPoint
member.summary: A contact point for a person or organization.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.CorrectionsPolicy
member.summary: For an Organization (e.g. NewsMediaOrganization), a statement describing (in news media, the newsrooms) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.CurrenciesAccepted
member.summary:
The currency accepted.

Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Department
member.summary: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.DissolutionDate
member.summary: The date that this organization was dissolved.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.DiversityPolicy
member.summary: Statement on diversity policy by an Organization e.g. a NewsMediaOrganization. For a NewsMediaOrganization, a statement describing the newsrooms diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.DiversityStaffingReport
member.summary: For an Organization (often but not necessarily a NewsMediaOrganization), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Duns
member.summary: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Email
member.summary: Email address.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Employee
member.summary: Someone working for this organization.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.EthicsPolicy
member.summary: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a NewsMediaOrganization regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a Restaurant, a page describing food source policies. In the case of a NewsMediaOrganization, an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Event
member.summary: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.FaxNumber
member.summary: The fax number.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Founder
member.summary: A person who founded this organization.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.FoundingDate
member.summary: The date that this organization was founded.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.FoundingLocation
member.summary: The place where the Organization was founded.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Funder
member.summary: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.GlobalLocationNumber
member.summary: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.HasOfferCatalog
member.summary: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.HasPOS
member.summary: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.IsicV4
member.summary: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.KnowsAbout
member.summary: Of a Person, and less typically of an Organization, to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or yet relate this to educational content, events, objectives or JobPosting descriptions.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.KnowsLanguage
member.summary: Of a Person, and less typically of an Organization, to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.LegalName
member.summary: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.LeiCode
member.summary: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Location
member.summary: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Logo
member.summary: An associated logo.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.MakesOffer
member.summary: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Member
member.summary: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.MemberOf
member.summary: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Naics
member.summary: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.NumberOfEmployees
member.summary: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.OpeningHours
member.summary:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.

  • Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
  • If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.OwnershipFundingInfo
member.summary: For an Organization (often but not necessarily a NewsMediaOrganization), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence. Note that the funder is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Owns
member.summary: Products owned by the organization or person.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.ParentOrganization
member.summary: The larger organization that this organization is a subOrganization of, if any.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.PaymentAccepted
member.summary: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.PriceRange
member.summary: The price range of the business, for example $$$.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.PublishingPrinciples
member.summary:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via URL) a document describing the editorial principles of an Organization (or individual e.g. a Person writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a CreativeWork (e.g. NewsArticle) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a funder) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Review
member.summary: A review of the item.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Seeks
member.summary: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Sponsor
member.summary: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.SubOrganization
member.summary: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.TaxID
member.summary: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.Telephone
member.summary: The telephone number.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.UnnamedSourcesPolicy
member.summary: For an Organization (typically a NewsMediaOrganization), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.LocalBusinessAndOrganization.VatID
member.summary: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.MedicalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization
member.summary: See MedicalBusiness, MedicalOrganization for more information.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.MedicalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.MedicalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.HealthPlanNetworkId
member.summary: Name or unique ID of network. (Networks are often reused across different insurance plans).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.MedicalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.IsAcceptingNewPatients
member.summary: Whether the provider is accepting new patients.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.MedicalBusinessAndMedicalOrganization.MedicalSpecialty
member.summary: A medical specialty of the provider.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DDxElement
member.summary: An alternative, closely-related condition typically considered later in the differential diagnosis process along with the signs that are used to distinguish it.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DDxElement.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DDxElement.Diagnosis
member.summary: One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process as output of a diagnosis process.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DDxElement.DistinguishingSign
member.summary: One of a set of signs and symptoms that can be used to distinguish this diagnosis from others in the differential diagnosis.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DiagnosticLab
member.summary: A medical laboratory that offers on-site or off-site diagnostic services.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DiagnosticLab.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DiagnosticLab.AvailableTest
member.summary: A diagnostic test or procedure offered by this lab.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DiagnosticProcedure
member.summary: A medical procedure intended primarily for diagnostic, as opposed to therapeutic, purposes.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DiagnosticProcedure.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.Diet
member.summary: A strategy of regulating the intake of food to achieve or maintain a specific health-related goal.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Diet.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Diet.DietFeatures
member.summary: Nutritional information specific to the dietary plan. May include dietary recommendations on what foods to avoid, what foods to consume, and specific alterations/deviations from the USDA or other regulatory body's approved dietary guidelines.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Diet.Endorsers
member.summary: People or organizations that endorse the plan.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Diet.ExpertConsiderations
member.summary: Medical expert advice related to the plan.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Diet.Overview
member.summary: Descriptive information establishing the overarching theory/philosophy of the plan. May include the rationale for the name, the population where the plan first came to prominence, etc.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Diet.PhysiologicalBenefits
member.summary: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Diet.Risks
member.summary: Specific physiologic risks associated to the diet plan.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement
member.summary: A product taken by mouth that contains a dietary ingredient intended to supplement the diet. Dietary ingredients may include vitamins, minerals, herbs or other botanicals, amino acids, and substances such as enzymes, organ tissues, glandulars and metabolites.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.ActiveIngredient
member.summary: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.Background
member.summary: Descriptive information establishing a historical perspective on the supplement. May include the rationale for the name, the population where the supplement first came to prominence, etc.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.IsProprietary
member.summary: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.LegalStatus
member.summary: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.MaximumIntake
member.summary: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.MechanismOfAction
member.summary: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.NonProprietaryName
member.summary: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.ProprietaryName
member.summary: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.RecommendedIntake
member.summary: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.SafetyConsideration
member.summary: Any potential safety concern associated with the supplement. May include interactions with other drugs and foods, pregnancy, breastfeeding, known adverse reactions, and documented efficacy of the supplement.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DietarySupplement.TargetPopulation
member.summary: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DoseSchedule
member.summary: A specific dosing schedule for a drug or supplement.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DoseSchedule.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DoseSchedule.DoseUnit
member.summary: The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DoseSchedule.DoseValue
member.summary: The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DoseSchedule.Frequency
member.summary: How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DoseSchedule.TargetPopulation
member.summary: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.Drug
member.summary: A chemical or biologic substance, used as a medical therapy, that has a physiological effect on an organism. Here the term drug is used interchangeably with the term medicine although clinical knowledge make a clear difference between them.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.ActiveIngredient
member.summary: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.AdministrationRoute
member.summary: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.AlcoholWarning
member.summary: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.AvailableStrength
member.summary: An available dosage strength for the drug.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.BreastfeedingWarning
member.summary: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.ClinicalPharmacology
member.summary: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.Cost
member.summary: Cost per unit of the drug, as reported by the source being tagged.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.DosageForm
member.summary: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.DoseSchedule
member.summary: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.DrugClass
member.summary: The class of drug this belongs to (e.g., statins).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.DrugUnit
member.summary: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.FoodWarning
member.summary: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of specific foods while taking this drug.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.InteractingDrug
member.summary: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.IsAvailableGenerically
member.summary: True if the drug is available in a generic form (regardless of name).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.IsProprietary
member.summary: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.LabelDetails
member.summary: Link to the drug's label details.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.LegalStatus
member.summary: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.MaximumIntake
member.summary: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.MechanismOfAction
member.summary: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.NonProprietaryName
member.summary: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.Overdosage
member.summary: Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.PregnancyCategory
member.summary: Pregnancy category of this drug.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.PregnancyWarning
member.summary: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.PrescribingInfo
member.summary: Link to prescribing information for the drug.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.PrescriptionStatus
member.summary: Indicates the status of drug prescription eg. local catalogs classifications or whether the drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter, etc.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.ProprietaryName
member.summary: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.RelatedDrug
member.summary: Any other drug related to this one, for example commonly-prescribed alternatives.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.Rxcui
member.summary: The RxCUI drug identifier from RXNORM.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.Drug.Warning
member.summary: Any FDA or other warnings about the drug (text or URL).

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DrugLegalStatus
member.summary: The legal availability status of a medical drug.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DrugLegalStatus.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DrugLegalStatus.ApplicableLocation
member.summary: The location in which the status applies.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DrugStrength
member.summary: A specific strength in which a medical drug is available in a specific country.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DrugStrength.Type
member.summary: Gets the name of the type as specified by schema.org.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DrugStrength.ActiveIngredient
member.summary: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DrugStrength.AvailableIn
member.summary: The location in which the strength is available.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DrugStrength.MaximumIntake
member.summary: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DrugStrength.StrengthUnit
member.summary: The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

member.name: P:Schema.NET.DrugStrength.StrengthValue
member.summary: The value of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. 325.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DrugClass
member.summary: A class of medical drugs, e.g., statins. Classes can represent general pharmacological class, common mechanisms of action, common physiological effects, etc.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DrugCost
member.summary: The cost per unit of a medical drug. Note that this type is not meant to represent the price in an offer of a drug for sale; see the Offer type for that. This type will typically be used to tag wholesale or average retail cost of a drug, or maximum reimbursable cost. Costs of medical drugs vary widely depending on how and where they are paid for, so while this type captures some of the variables, costs should be used with caution by consumers of this schema's markup.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DrugCostCategory
member.summary: Enumerated categories of medical drug costs.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugCostCategory.ReimbursementCap
member.summary: The drug's cost represents the maximum reimbursement paid by an insurer for the drug.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugCostCategory.Retail
member.summary: The drug's cost represents the retail cost of the drug.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugCostCategory.Wholesale

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DrugPregnancyCategory
member.summary: Categories that represent an assessment of the risk of fetal injury due to a drug or pharmaceutical used as directed by the mother during pregnancy.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugPregnancyCategory.FDAcategoryA
member.summary: A designation by the US FDA signifying that adequate and well-controlled studies have failed to demonstrate a risk to the fetus in the first trimester of pregnancy (and there is no evidence of risk in later trimesters).

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugPregnancyCategory.FDAcategoryB
member.summary: A designation by the US FDA signifying that animal reproduction studies have failed to demonstrate a risk to the fetus and there are no adequate and well-controlled studies in pregnant women.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugPregnancyCategory.FDAcategoryC
member.summary: A designation by the US FDA signifying that animal reproduction studies have shown an adverse effect on the fetus and there are no adequate and well-controlled studies in humans, but potential benefits may warrant use of the drug in pregnant women despite potential risks.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugPregnancyCategory.FDAcategoryD
member.summary: A designation by the US FDA signifying that there is positive evidence of human fetal risk based on adverse reaction data from investigational or marketing experience or studies in humans, but potential benefits may warrant use of the drug in pregnant women despite potential risks.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugPregnancyCategory.FDAcategoryX
member.summary: A designation by the US FDA signifying that studies in animals or humans have demonstrated fetal abnormalities and/or there is positive evidence of human fetal risk based on adverse reaction data from investigational or marketing experience, and the risks involved in use of the drug in pregnant women clearly outweigh potential benefits.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugPregnancyCategory.FDAnotEvaluated
member.summary: A designation that the drug in question has not been assigned a pregnancy category designation by the US FDA.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.DrugPrescriptionStatus

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugPrescriptionStatus.OTC

member.name: F:Schema.NET.DrugPrescriptionStatus.PrescriptionOnly

member.name: F:Schema.NET.InfectiousAgentClass.Protozoa

member.name: F:Schema.NET.InfectiousAgentClass.Virus
member.summary: Pathogenic virus that causes viral infection.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.MedicalImagingTechnique

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalImagingTechnique.XRay

member.name: T:Schema.NET.MedicalObservationalStudyDesign
member.summary: Design models for observational medical studies. Enumerated type.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalObservationalStudyDesign.CaseSeries
member.summary: A case series (also known as a clinical series) is a medical research study that tracks patients with a known exposure given similar treatment or examines their medical records for exposure and outcome. A case series can be retrospective or prospective and usually involves a smaller number of patients than the more powerful case-control studies or randomized controlled trials. Case series may be consecutive or non-consecutive, depending on whether all cases presenting to the reporting authors over a period of time were included, or only a selection.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalObservationalStudyDesign.CohortStudy
member.summary: Also known as a panel study. A cohort study is a form of longitudinal study used in medicine and social science. It is one type of study design and should be compared with a cross-sectional study. A cohort is a group of people who share a common characteristic or experience within a defined period (e.g., are born, leave school, lose their job, are exposed to a drug or a vaccine, etc.). The comparison group may be the general population from which the cohort is drawn, or it may be another cohort of persons thought to have had little or no exposure to the substance under investigation, but otherwise similar. Alternatively, subgroups within the cohort may be compared with each other.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalObservationalStudyDesign.CrossSectional
member.summary: Studies carried out on pre-existing data (usually from 'snapshot' surveys), such as that collected by the Census Bureau. Sometimes called Prevalence Studies.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalObservationalStudyDesign.Longitudinal
member.summary: Unlike cross-sectional studies, longitudinal studies track the same people, and therefore the differences observed in those people are less likely to be the result of cultural differences across generations. Longitudinal studies are also used in medicine to uncover predictors of certain diseases.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalObservationalStudyDesign.Observational
member.summary: An observational study design.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalObservationalStudyDesign.Registry
member.summary: A registry-based study design.

member.name: T:Schema.NET.MedicalProcedureType

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalProcedureType.NoninvasiveProcedure

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalProcedureType.PercutaneousProcedure

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Cardiovascular

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Dentistry

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Dermatology

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.DietNutrition

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Emergency

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Endocrine

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Gastroenterologic

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Genetic

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Geriatric
member.summary: A specific branch of medical science that is concerned with the diagnosis and treatment of diseases, debilities and provision of care to the aged.

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Gynecologic

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Hematologic

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Infectious

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Midwifery

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Musculoskeletal

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Neurologic

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Nursing

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Obstetric

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Oncologic

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Otolaryngologic

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.Pathology

member.name: F:Schema.NET.MedicalSpecialty.PlasticSurgery
